# Initialize an empty list to store data frames
dfs <- list()

# Iterate over each file
for (file in filtered_files) {
  file_path <- file.path(directory, file)
  tryCatch({
    df <- read.csv(file_path)
    if (length(dfs) > 0) {
      if (!all(names(df) == names(dfs[[1]]))) {
        stop(paste("Columns of", file, "do not match previous files."))
      }
    }
    dfs <- append(dfs, list(df))
  }, error = function(e) {
    message(paste("Error reading", file, ":", e$message))
  })
}

# Combine data frames if there are any valid ones
if (length(dfs) > 0) {
  combined_df <- bind_rows(dfs)
  print(dim(combined_df))
} else {
  print("No valid CSV files found.")
}

# Filter rows where the score matches the expected format
filtered_df <- filtered_df[grepl("^\\d+-\\d+(\\s\\d+-\\d+)*$", filtered_df$score), ]
# Split 'score' column into separate sets
filtered_df$sets <- strsplit(filtered_df$score, "\\s+")
winner_scores <- numeric(nrow(filtered_df))
loser_scores <- numeric(nrow(filtered_df))
for (i in 1:nrow(filtered_df)) {
  winner_score <- 0
  loser_score <- 0
  # Iterate over sets in 'sets' column
  for (set_score in filtered_df$sets[[i]]) {
    scores <- as.integer(strsplit(set_score, "-")[[1]])
    if (scores[1] > scores[2]) {
      winner_score <- winner_score + 1
    } else {
      loser_score <- loser_score + 1
    }
  }
  winner_scores[i] <- winner_score
  loser_scores[i] <- loser_score
}
filtered_df$winner_score <- winner_scores
filtered_df$loser_score <- loser_scores
filtered_df <- subset(filtered_df, select = -c(score, sets))
filtered_df[, c('winner_score', 'loser_score')]
# Initialize a vector to store outcomes
outcome <- numeric(nrow(filtered_df))

# Iterate over each pair of winner_score and loser_score
for (i in 1:nrow(filtered_df)) {
  if (filtered_df$winner_score[i] > filtered_df$loser_score[i]) {
    outcome[i] <- 1  # Winner
  } else {
    outcome[i] <- 0  # Loser
  }
}

# Add the outcome column to filtered_df
filtered_df$outcome <- outcome

# Create an indicator for whether the higher-ranked player won
filtered_df <- filtered_df %>%
  mutate(higher_rank_won = as.numeric(winner_rank < loser_rank)) %>%
  mutate(higher_rank_points = winner_rank_points * higher_rank_won +
           loser_rank_points * (1 - higher_rank_won)) %>%
  mutate(lower_rank_points = winner_rank_points * (1 - higher_rank_won) +
           loser_rank_points * higher_rank_won)
# Create a new variable for the difference in points
filtered_df <- filtered_df %>%
  mutate(diff = higher_rank_points - lower_rank_points)

# Split data into training and test sets based on 'tourney_date'

# Install and load necessary libraries
if (!requireNamespace("tidyverse", quietly = TRUE)) {
  install.packages("tidyverse")
}
library(tidyverse)
# Initialize Elo ratings for all players
initial_elo <- 1500
elo_ratings <- filtered_df %>%
  select(winner_name, loser_name) %>%
  gather(key = "role", value = "player") %>%
  distinct(player) %>%
  mutate(elo = initial_elo)
# Merge Elo ratings with the match data
filtered_df <- filtered_df %>%
  left_join(elo_ratings, by = c("winner_name" = "player")) %>%
  rename(winner_elo = elo) %>%
  left_join(elo_ratings, by = c("loser_name" = "player")) %>%
  rename(loser_elo = elo)
# Define the K-factor
k_factor <- 25

# Function to calculate the expected outcome
expected_outcome <- function(winner_elo, loser_elo) {
  1 / (1 + 10 ^ ((loser_elo - winner_elo) / 400))
}

# Iterate over each match and update Elo ratings
for (i in 1:nrow(filtered_df)) {
  winner_elo <- filtered_df$winner_elo[i]
  loser_elo <- filtered_df$loser_elo[i]
  expected_win <- expected_outcome(winner_elo, loser_elo)
  
  # Update Elo ratings
  filtered_df$winner_elo[i] <- winner_elo + k_factor * (1 - expected_win)
  filtered_df$loser_elo[i] <- loser_elo - k_factor * (1 - expected_win)
  
  # Update Elo ratings in the elo_ratings data frame
  elo_ratings <- elo_ratings %>%
    mutate(elo = case_when(
      player == filtered_df$winner_name[i] ~ filtered_df$winner_elo[i],
      player == filtered_df$loser_name[i] ~ filtered_df$loser_elo[i],
      TRUE ~ elo
    ))
}
# Merge updated Elo ratings back into the filtered_df
filtered_df <- filtered_df %>%
  left_join(elo_ratings, by = c("winner_name" = "player")) %>%
  rename(final_winner_elo = elo) %>%
  left_join(elo_ratings, by = c("loser_name" = "player")) %>%
  rename(final_loser_elo = elo)
# Calculate the prediction probabilities
filtered_df <- filtered_df %>%
  mutate(pred_prob = expected_outcome(final_winner_elo, final_loser_elo))
# Calculate accuracy
accuracy <- mean((filtered_df$pred_prob > 0.5) == filtered_df$higher_rank_won)
cat("Accuracy:", accuracy, "\n")
Accuracy: 0.4880283 
# Calculate log-loss
log_loss <- -mean(filtered_df$higher_rank_won * log(filtered_df$pred_prob) +
                  (1 - filtered_df$higher_rank_won) * log(1 - filtered_df$pred_prob))
cat("Log-loss:", log_loss, "\n")
